abstract: >-
  This dataset contains the complete validation results for EVAonline, 
  an open-source Kalman fusion system for reference evapotranspiration (ETo) 
  estimation in Brazil. The dataset includes daily ETo values from four sources:
  (1) Xavier et al. BR-DWGD reference data (Brazilian Daily Weather Gridded Data,
  1961-2024, 0.1° resolution, 3,625+ weather stations), (2) NASA POWER reanalysis
  (MERRA-2, 0.5° resolution), (3) Open-Meteo Archive (ERA5-Land, ~9km resolution),
  and (4) EVAonline Kalman fusion results. Data covers 16 Brazilian cities in the
  MATOPIBA region plus Piracicaba (São Paulo) spanning 1991-2020, totaling 186,287
  daily observations. EVAonline demonstrates superior performance with MAE=0.42 mm/day,
  PBIAS=0.71%, and KGE=0.814, significantly outperforming NASA POWER (MAE=0.84,
  PBIAS=15.78%, KGE=0.411) and Open-Meteo (MAE=0.86, PBIAS=13.02%, KGE=0.432).
  The hybrid Kalman fusion achieves 38.7-50.8% MAE reduction and 91.4-95.5% BIAS
  reduction compared to individual sources. The repository includes raw data,
  validation scripts, statistical analyses, and reproducible Jupyter notebooks.
